It can be hard to know which packages you need. Google is the best tool, or ask on Software Underground — the chances are that someone can help. In the meantime, here are the packages you definitely need to know about:
Image object, image loading, saving, and manipulation.
Plotting.
Regular expressions.
Lightweight web apps.
Quick web requests.
Linear algebraic functions accessing BLAS and LAPACK, eg dot and norm.
Various Fourier transform tools, eg fft, fft2, fftfreq, fftshift, and ifft.
n-dimensional interpolation and spline-fitting.
Spatial analysis algorithms, such as triangulation and KD-tree.
Signal processing, including 2D convolution, Hilbert transform, and filtering.
Functions for multi-dimensional image processing, including nonlinear filters.
Jupyter environment.
Testing framework.
Make documentation.
Graph theoretic networks, operations and plotting.
